						               													<description>It&amp;rsquo;s 1848 and all anyone can talk about are the rumors of gold being found in the Sacramento Valley. Now&amp;rsquo;s your chance to try to get a piece of the prize, so grab your tools and start digging!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rumors of Gold is a solo roll &amp;amp; write game set in the California gold rush of 1848. The player aims to get rich by digging for the most valuable resources and panning for gold.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn, the player rolls three dice and uses them to explore a new area. The dice values are also used to build up the value of key resources &amp;ndash; copper, silver, and gems &amp;ndash; which can maximize the output of each dig. In addition, the player acquires rumors of gold, which can yield valuable riches when exploring the right river areas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player uses the dice values, and modifiers gained through the game, to choose the best times and locations to collect resources. When the player can no longer explore a new area, they add up their gold and the value of their completed digs to get their final score.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
